The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. Key Developments

The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. Presents at Stifel 2017 Technology, Internet & Media Conference, Jun-05-2017 01:15 PM
May 31 17
The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. Presents at Stifel 2017 Technology, Internet & Media Conference, Jun-05-2017 01:15 PM. Venue: Fairmont San Francisco, 950 Mason Street, San Francisco, California, United States. Speakers: Mitchell K. Dauerman, Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice President and Treasurer.


The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. Presents at The William Blair 2017 Growth Stock Conference, Jun-13-2017 12:10 PM
May 31 17
The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. Presents at The William Blair 2017 Growth Stock Conference, Jun-13-2017 12:10 PM. Venue: The Four Seasons Hotel, 120 East Delaware Place, Chicago, IL 60611, United States. Speakers: Mitchell K. Dauerman, Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice President and Treasurer, Scott Scherr, Founder, Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President.


Year-Round Alaskan Resort Uses Ultimate Software's Ultipro to Reduce Costs, Improve People Operations
May 15 17
Ultimate Software announced that Alyeska Resort, Alaska's premier year-round destination, is using UltiPro to enhance strategic planning and enable managers and HR to offer greater business value. Alyeska Resort's proximity to Anchorage provides travelers with easy access to the destination's summer and winter events, such as skiing, meetings, and weddings. Prior to UltiPro, the company was using separate systems for payroll and timekeeping, which were inaccessible to anyone outside accounting and payroll. Alyeska sought a comprehensive HCM solution that would enable managers to analyze and better understand seasonal labor patterns and control costs, and to improve people operations with role-based access for supervisors. Alyeska selected UltiPro and went live in May 2014. Alyeska is taking advantage of UltiPro's Business Intelligence Knowledge Exchange to extend their reporting capabilities for strategic planning. This forum allows UltiPro users from anywhere in the world to share the innovative reports they have created. Alyeska is taking advantage of this knowledge sharing program to enhance their reports related to time management and compliance. Hawes reports that Alyeska is not only using UltiPro's flexibility to enhance reporting, but also to substantially reduce managers administrative tasks.


