In Volatile Markets Do Analysts Think You Should Buy The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI)?


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Friday, 21 Jul 2017 09:31 AM  / 0 Comments




Following U.S. election volatility some analysts have updated their recommended target prices on shares of The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI).  	 According to the most recently released broker notes, 7 analysts have a rating of “strong buy” on the stock, 12 analysts “buy”, 6 analysts “neutral”, 0 analysts “sell” and 0 analysts “strong sell”. 	  



Latest Recommended Buy/Sell Side Ratings:
07/19/2017 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Piper Jaffray.  They now have a USD 250 price target on the stock.
07/03/2017 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Credit Suisse. 
06/26/2017 – SunTrust began new coverage on The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 240 price target on the stock.
06/26/2017 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Pacific Crest.  They now have a USD 255 price target on the stock.
05/11/2017 – Wells Fargo began new coverage on The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 240 price target on the stock.
04/26/2017 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Wedbush.  They now have a USD 236 price target on the stock.
04/13/2017 – Guggenheim began new coverage on The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 230 price target on the stock.
04/11/2017 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at MKM Partners.  They now have a USD 250 price target on the stock.
03/03/2017 – Mizuho began new coverage on The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. giving the company a “” rating.
02/08/2017 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Needham & Company.  They now have a USD 250 price target on the stock.
02/07/2017 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at William Blair. 
07/27/2016 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Deutsche Bank.  They now have a USD 240 price target on the stock.
07/27/2016 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Stifel Nicolaus.  They now have a USD 235 price target on the stock.
07/27/2016 – The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at UBS.  They now have a USD 250 price target on the stock.
05/23/2016 – Goldman Sachs began new coverage on The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 196 price target on the stock.
The share price of The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) was up +0.51% during the last trading session, with a day high of 225.19. 237841 shares were traded on The Ultimate Software Group, Inc.’s last session. 
The stock’s 50 day moving average is 215.79 and its 200 day moving average is 203.88. The stock’s market capitalization is 6.67B. The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. has a 52-week low of 180.29 and a 52-week high of 225.62.



The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (Ultimate) is a cloud provider of people management solutions, referred to as human capital management (HCM). The Company’s UltiPro product suite (UltiPro) is an engaging solution that has human resources (HR), payroll and benefits management. As of December 31, 2016, UltiPro included global people management, available in 14 languages with more than 35 country-specific localizations. The solution is delivered through software-as-a-service (SaaS) to organizations based in the United States and Canada, including those with global workforces. The UltiPro solution includes feature sets for talent acquisition and onboarding, HR management and compliance, benefits management and online enrollment, payroll, performance management, compensation management with salary planning, budgeting, and development of incentive plans, succession management, reporting and analytical decision-making and predictive tools, and time and attendance.


