The Ultimate Software Group, In (NASDAQ:ULTI) Sees Significantly Higher Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsThe Ultimate Software Group, In (NASDAQ:ULTI) Sees Significantly Higher Trading Volume
July 20, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Trading volume for The Ultimate Software Group, In was 428K in the last trading session.  Trading volume was up 103.71% over the stocks average daily volume. 
 Here are some other firms who have updated their holdings.   As of the end of the quarter Peregrine Capital Management LLC had sold  a total of 247 shares trimming its holdings by 0.2%. The value in dollars increased from $27,398,000 to $29,438,000 a change of $2,040,000 for the reporting period. As of quarter end Sit Investment Associates Inc had disposed of 1,285 shares trimming its stake by 4.5%. The value of the investment in (ULTI) went from $5,559,000 to $5,712,000 a change of 2.8% quarter to quarter.
 As of the end of the quarter Aperio Group, LLC had acquired  a total of 7,199 shares growing its position 43.9%. The value of the investment in ULTI increased from $3,205,000 to $4,961,000 increasing 54.8% since the last quarter. As of the end of the quarter State Treasurer State Of Michigan had bought  a total of 100 shares growing its holdings by 0.8%. The value of the total investment in The Ultimate Software Group, In increased from $2,362,000 to $2,563,000 a change of 8.5% quarter over quarter.
  On June 26 analysts at SunTrust Robinson Humphrey started covering ULTI setting a rating of “Buy”. Wells Fargo started covering the stock by announcing an initial rating of “Outperform”.        Advertisement






 On October 31 the company was upgraded to “Outperform” from “” in a report issued by Wedbush. On September 20, 2016 Pacific Crest added ULTI to its research portfolio giving it an initial rating of “Overweight”.
 Equity analyst Pacific Crest started coverage with an initial rating of “Overweight”. Piper Jaffray initiated coverage with a rating of “Overweight” and price target of $225.00.
 The company is so far trading up by 3.92% since yesterday’s close of $215.06.  Shares are trading at $223.48 barely above the 50 day moving average which is $215.68 and which is just a bit higher than the 200 day moving average of $203.73.  The 50 day moving average went up $7.80 or +3.62% and the 200 day average was up $19.75. 
 The P/E ratio is currently 221.27 and market cap is 6.64B.  As of the last earnings report the EPS was $1.01 and is estimated to be $3.98 for the current year with 29,715,000 shares now outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $1.07 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $4.93. 
 The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (Ultimate), launched on April 15, 1996, is a cloud provider of people management solutions, referred to as human capital management (HCM). The Business’s UltiPro product suite (UltiPro) is an engaging solution that has human resources (HR), payroll and benefits management. As of December 31, 2016, UltiPro included people management, available in 14 languages with more than 35 country-specific localizations. The solution is delivered through software-as-a-service (SaaS) to organizations based in the United States and Canada, including those with global workforces..
