BidaskClub Downgrades The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (ULTI) to Buy

		Posted by James Conley on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 



Tweet










The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) was downgraded by BidaskClub from a “strong-buy” rating to a “buy” rating in a research note issued on Friday, June 30th.
Several other equities analysts have also weighed in on the company. Zacks Investment Research raised The Ultimate Software Group from a “strong sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Wednesday, June 28th. SunTrust Banks, Inc. assumed coverage on The Ultimate Software Group in a report on Monday, June 26th. They set a “buy” rating and a $240.00 price objective for the company. Pacific Crest  reissued an “overweight” rating and set a $255.00 price objective (up from $240.00) on shares of The Ultimate Software Group in a report on Monday, June 26th. ValuEngine raised The Ultimate Software Group from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Friday, June 2nd. Finally, Royal Bank Of Canada  reissued a “buy” rating and set a $233.00 price objective on shares of The Ultimate Software Group in a report on Monday, May 29th. Three analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and sixteen have assigned  a buy rating to the stock. The company  has an average rating of “Buy” and an average target price of $240.07.


 Get The Ultimate Software Group Inc. alerts:



The Ultimate Software Group (NASDAQ ULTI) traded up 0.34% during mid-day trading on Friday, reaching $225.39. The company had a trading volume of 223,494 shares. The stock has a 50-day moving average of $215.79 and a 200 day moving average of $203.88. The Ultimate Software Group has a 12-month low of $180.29 and a 12-month high of $227.16. The company has a market capitalization of $6.70 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 223.16 and a beta of 1.07. 




The Ultimate Software Group (NASDAQ:ULTI) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, April 25th. The technology company reported $0.75 EPS for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.73 by $0.02. The Ultimate Software Group had a return on equity of 6.88% and a net margin of 3.23%. The company had revenue of $228.49 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $228.87 million. During the same period last year, the business posted $0.73 earnings per share. The Ultimate Software Group’s revenue was up 22.0% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, analysts expect that  The Ultimate Software Group will post $3.98 EPS for the current year. 
