ULTI - Market Data & News
ULTI - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

The Ultimate Software Group Inc. (ULTI) traded on unusually high volume on Jun. 29, as the stock 
lost 3.19% to close at $209.94. On the day, The Ultimate Software Group Inc. saw 596,365 shares trade hands on 4,358 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 250,420 shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $225.63 and $180.29 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $213.27, and its 200-day SMA $202.08. The Ultimate Software Group Inc. 
has a P/B ratio of 14.11. It also has a P/E ratio of 249.3.  


The Ultimate Software Group Inc is a cloud provider of people management solutions. Its UltiPro product suite is a comprehensive, engaging solution that has human resources, payroll, and benefits management at its core and includes people management.

Headquartered in Weston, FL, The Ultimate Software Group Inc. has 3,747 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO Scott Scherr.


For a complete fundamental analysis analysis of The Ultimate Software Group Inc., check out Equities.com’s Stock Valuation Analysis report 
for ULTI.

